From johnson George Johnson Subject monitor jitter Several weeks ago I described a problem with my Apple High Resolution monitor and promised to summarize replies received by e To recapitulate Occasionally every two or three hours or so my monitor momentarily loses The entire raster image bounces down about an eighth of an inch or so then rights This usually happens right after I close a large window highlight a large area or do something that radically alters the image on the Sometimes though it happens with no provocation I have received a bewildering range of At one extreme was a man clearly quite knowledgable about monitors who said that the problem was that the monitor's power supply simply couldn't always keep up with sudden changes of the raster image the rapid change from a largely light screen to a largely dark one overtaxed the monitor's power There was no fix available he said because nothing was really I guess he meant that the flaw was so fundamental that it had to be This seemed quite persuasive and I would have been tempted to adopt an attitude of stoicism except for a reply from a monitor owner who discovered that this very problem is documented in the Apple Service Technical Procedures Volume under the heading Jitter The section describes a fix involving the replacement of a capacitor the adjustment of a potentiometer or failing that the swap of a circuit I would be grateful for a discussion among those who have had experience with this sort of